alert.note: Alert for Coastal Dixie; Coastal Taylor (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued December 23 at 11:48AM EST until December 23 at 4:00PM EST by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 4 PM EST THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Minor coastal flooding. * WHERE...Coastal Taylor and Coastal Dixie Counties. * WHEN...Until 4 PM EST this afternoon. * IMPACTS...Water levels will rise to 2 to 2.5 feet mean higher high water around the time of high tide. These water levels will result in minor flooding in Steinhatchee, Horseshoe Beach, and Suwannee. In Suwannee, water will likely overtop some canals flooding low lying areas and roadways in the community.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property.
